    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Review the program. The `Painter` collects paint, turns left, and then enters a `while` loop.\r\n\r\n   * Inside the loop, the `Painter` checks if it has paint.\r\n   \r\n   * If it does, it paints and moves forward.\r\n   \r\n   * But if it's out of paint, it does **nothing**, and the loop runs forever!\r\n\r\n2. Add an `else` statement so the `Painter` moves forward even if it doesn't have paint.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/ae25db1a5ea932bf0ebc4b3a94fc7ee7-choiceB.gif)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nEvery loop should move the `Painter` forward in some way, otherwise the loop might repeat forever. Use `else` to make sure something *always* happens.",
